.TH erf 3
.SH NAME
.PP
\*Lerf\*O, \*Lerfc\*O \- Error functions
.SH LIBRARY
.PP
\*OMath Library (\*Llibm.a\*O)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
.sS
\*L#include <math.h>
.PP
\*Ldouble erf   (\*Ldouble \*Vx\*L);
.nL
\*Lfloat  erff  (\*Lfloat  \*Vx\*L);
.nL
\*Ldouble erfc  (\*Ldouble \*Vx\*L);
.nL
\*Lfloat  erfcf (\*Lfloat  \*Vx\*L);
.sE
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.iX "error function"
\*Lerf(\|)\*O and \*Lerff(\|)\*O
return the error function of \*Vx\*O; where erf(\*Vx\*O)
and erff(\*Vx\*O) equal (2 * sqrt(pi)) times the area under the
curve e**(-t**2) between 0 and \*Vx\*O.
.PP
\*Lerfc(\|)\*O and \*Lerfcf(\|)\*O
return (1.0 - erf (\*Vx\*O)).
.PP
EXCEPTIONAL CASES
.PP
None
.EQ
delim off
.EN
